---
const tagline = "Synthetic libraries can't gate the safety case — the ground truth is circular. Skydock is the curated, criticality-scored, validation-grade aerial BEV scenario library that AV safety teams use to close their closed-loop collision-rate gates.";
const subline = "Continuous capture from fixed-point installations at high-incident US intersections. Filtered through a 5-signal curation pipeline. Indexed against your OpenODD coverage model. Delivered as a subscription, not a pile of clips.";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/favicon.svg`} />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <meta name="generator" content={Astro.generator} />
    <meta name="description" content={tagline} />
    <meta property="og:title" content="Skydock — Validation-grade aerial BEV scenario library for AV safety teams" />
    <meta property="og:description" content={tagline} />
    <meta property="og:type" content="website" />
    <title>Skydock — Validation-grade aerial BEV scenario library</title>
    <style is:global>
      :root {
        --bg: #0a0e1a;
        --bg-elev: #111827;
        --border: #1f2937;
        --text: #e5e7eb;
        --text-dim: #9ca3af;
        --text-strong: #f9fafb;
        --accent: #60a5fa;
        --accent-dim: #1e3a8a;
        --accent-soft: rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.08);
        --good: #9ee37d;
        --warn: #e5b85a;
        --mono: 'SF Mono', 'Monaco', 'Cascadia Code', 'Roboto Mono', Menlo, Consolas, monospace;
        --sans: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif;
      }
      * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
      html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }
      body {
        background: var(--bg);
        color: var(--text);
        font-family: var(--sans);
        line-height: 1.65;
        font-size: 17px;
        -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
        text-rendering: optimizeLegibility;
      }
      a {
        color: var(--accent);
        text-decoration: none;
        border-bottom: 1px solid transparent;
        transition: border-color 0.15s ease;
      }
      a:hover { border-bottom-color: var(--accent); }
      .container {
        max-width: 820px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 0 24px;
      }
      header.site-header {
        padding: 24px 0;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
        position: sticky;
        top: 0;
        background: var(--bg);
        z-index: 10;
      }
      .site-header .row {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: space-between;
      }
      .brand {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 18px;
        letter-spacing: 0.02em;
        color: var(--text-strong);
      }
      .brand::before {
        content: '◆ ';
        color: var(--accent);
      }
      .nav {
        display: flex;
        gap: 24px;
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 13px;
      }
      .nav a {
        color: var(--text-dim);
        border-bottom: none;
      }
      .nav a:hover { color: var(--accent); }
      @media (max-width: 600px) {
        .nav { display: none; }
      }
      section.hero { padding: 96px 0 56px; }
      h1 {
        font-size: clamp(36px, 6vw, 60px);
        font-weight: 700;
        line-height: 1.05;
        letter-spacing: -0.02em;
        margin-bottom: 28px;
        color: var(--text-strong);
      }
      .hero p.tagline {
        font-size: 22px;
        color: var(--text);
        max-width: 680px;
        margin-bottom: 22px;
        line-height: 1.4;
      }
      .hero p.subline {
        font-size: 17px;
        color: var(--text-dim);
        max-width: 680px;
      }
      .hero-meta {
        margin-top: 32px;
        display: flex;
        gap: 28px;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 12px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.08em;
        color: var(--text-dim);
      }
      .hero-meta .label { color: var(--accent); margin-right: 8px; }
      section {
        padding: 64px 0;
        border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
      }
      h2 {
        font-size: 13px;
        font-family: var(--mono);
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.14em;
        color: var(--accent);
        margin-bottom: 24px;
        font-weight: 500;
      }
      h3 {
        font-size: 26px;
        font-weight: 600;
        margin-bottom: 18px;
        letter-spacing: -0.01em;
        color: var(--text-strong);
        line-height: 1.3;
      }
      h4 {
        font-size: 18px;
        font-weight: 600;
        margin-bottom: 10px;
        color: var(--text-strong);
      }
      p { margin-bottom: 18px; color: var(--text); }
      p.dim { color: var(--text-dim); }
      strong { color: var(--text-strong); font-weight: 600; }

      blockquote.pullquote {
        border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
        padding: 12px 0 12px 24px;
        margin: 28px 0;
        font-size: 19px;
        color: var(--text);
        font-style: italic;
        line-height: 1.5;
      }
      blockquote.pullquote .attribution {
        display: block;
        margin-top: 10px;
        font-style: normal;
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 12px;
        color: var(--text-dim);
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      }

      ul.feature-list {
        list-style: none;
        margin: 24px 0;
      }
      ul.feature-list li {
        padding: 14px 0;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
        display: flex;
        gap: 18px;
        align-items: baseline;
      }
      ul.feature-list li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
      ul.feature-list .key {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 13px;
        color: var(--accent);
        min-width: 170px;
        flex-shrink: 0;
      }
      ul.feature-list .val { color: var(--text); }

      table.compare {
        width: 100%;
        border-collapse: collapse;
        margin: 24px 0;
        font-size: 14px;
      }
      table.compare th,
      table.compare td {
        text-align: left;
        padding: 12px 12px;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
        vertical-align: top;
      }
      table.compare th {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 11px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.08em;
        color: var(--accent);
        font-weight: 500;
        background: var(--accent-soft);
      }
      table.compare td.headline {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        color: var(--text-strong);
        white-space: nowrap;
      }
      table.compare tr.skydock-row {
        background: rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.06);
      }
      table.compare tr.skydock-row td.headline { color: var(--accent); }

      table.pricing {
        width: 100%;
        border-collapse: collapse;
        margin: 24px 0;
        font-size: 15px;
      }
      table.pricing th,
      table.pricing td {
        text-align: left;
        padding: 14px 16px;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
      }
      table.pricing th {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 11px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.08em;
        color: var(--text-dim);
        font-weight: 500;
      }
      table.pricing td.tier {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        color: var(--text-strong);
      }
      table.pricing td.price {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        color: var(--accent);
        font-weight: 600;
        white-space: nowrap;
      }

      .deliverable-card {
        background: var(--bg-elev);
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 8px;
        padding: 22px;
        margin: 24px 0;
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 13.5px;
        line-height: 1.7;
      }
      .deliverable-card .tree-line { color: var(--text-dim); }
      .deliverable-card .file { color: var(--accent); }
      .deliverable-card .desc { color: var(--text-dim); }

      .scene-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr));
        gap: 12px;
        margin: 24px 0;
      }
      .scene-tag {
        background: var(--bg-elev);
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 6px;
        padding: 12px 14px;
      }
      .scene-tag .name {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 13px;
        color: var(--accent);
        margin-bottom: 4px;
      }
      .scene-tag .desc {
        font-size: 13px;
        color: var(--text-dim);
        line-height: 1.4;
      }

      ul.faq-list {
        list-style: none;
        margin: 24px 0;
      }

      .pack-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr));
        gap: 16px;
        margin: 20px 0 32px;
      }
      .pack-card {
        background: var(--bg-elev);
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 8px;
        padding: 22px 22px 24px;
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 8px;
      }
      .pack-card.featured {
        border-color: var(--accent);
        background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(96,165,250,0.04), var(--bg-elev));
      }
      .pack-card .pack-name {
        font-size: 17px;
        font-weight: 600;
        color: var(--text-strong);
        margin-bottom: 2px;
      }
      .pack-card .pack-includes {
        font-size: 13.5px;
        color: var(--text-dim);
        line-height: 1.5;
        margin-bottom: 6px;
      }
      .pack-card .pack-meta {
        display: flex;
        justify-content: space-between;
        align-items: baseline;
        padding-top: 12px;
        border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
        margin-top: auto;
      }
      .pack-card .pack-count {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 12px;
        color: var(--text-dim);
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      }
      .pack-card .pack-price {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 18px;
        color: var(--accent);
        font-weight: 600;
      }

      h4.subsection {
        font-size: 14px;
        font-family: var(--mono);
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.1em;
        color: var(--text-strong);
        margin-top: 28px;
        margin-bottom: 12px;
        font-weight: 500;
      }
      h4.subsection:first-of-type { margin-top: 8px; }
      h4.subsection .tier-label {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 11px;
        color: var(--text-dim);
        text-transform: lowercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.02em;
        font-weight: 400;
        margin-left: 8px;
      }
      ul.faq-list li {
        padding: 18px 0;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
      }
      ul.faq-list li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
      .faq-q {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 14px;
        color: var(--accent);
        margin-bottom: 8px;
        font-weight: 500;
      }
      .faq-a {
        color: var(--text);
        font-size: 16px;
        line-height: 1.55;
      }

      .sources-group {
        margin: 24px 0;
      }
      .sources-group h4 {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 12px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.1em;
        color: var(--accent);
        font-weight: 500;
        margin-bottom: 14px;
        padding-bottom: 8px;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
      }
      .sources-group ul {
        list-style: none;
        margin: 0;
      }
      .sources-group ul li {
        padding: 8px 0;
        font-size: 13px;
        color: var(--text-dim);
        line-height: 1.5;
      }
      .sources-group ul li a {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 13px;
        color: var(--text);
      }
      .sources-group ul li .src-note {
        color: var(--text-dim);
        margin-left: 6px;
      }

      ul.sla-list { list-style: none; margin: 18px 0 24px; }
      ul.sla-list li {
        padding: 10px 0 10px 30px;
        position: relative;
        color: var(--text);
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
      }
      ul.sla-list li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
      ul.sla-list li::before {
        content: "✓";
        position: absolute;
        left: 0;
        top: 10px;
        color: var(--good);
        font-weight: 600;
      }
      ul.sla-list .pct {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        color: var(--accent);
        font-weight: 600;
      }

      .pilot-card {
        background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(96,165,250,0.06), var(--bg-elev));
        border: 1px solid var(--accent);
        border-radius: 8px;
        padding: 28px;
        margin: 28px 0;
      }
      .pilot-card .pilot-step {
        display: flex;
        gap: 18px;
        padding: 14px 0;
        align-items: baseline;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
      }
      .pilot-card .pilot-step:last-of-type { border-bottom: none; }
      .pilot-card .pilot-step .step-num {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 13px;
        color: var(--accent);
        min-width: 60px;
        flex-shrink: 0;
      }
      .pilot-card .pilot-step .step-body { color: var(--text); }
      .pilot-card .pilot-headline {
        font-size: 18px;
        font-weight: 600;
        color: var(--text-strong);
        margin-bottom: 14px;
      }

      .contact-card {
        background: var(--bg-elev);
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 8px;
        padding: 30px;
        margin: 24px 0;
      }
      .contact-card .name {
        font-size: 22px;
        font-weight: 600;
        margin-bottom: 4px;
        color: var(--text-strong);
      }
      .contact-card .role {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 13px;
        color: var(--text-dim);
        margin-bottom: 18px;
      }
      .contact-card .bio { font-size: 16px; color: var(--text-dim); margin-bottom: 22px; }
      .contact-links { display: flex; gap: 24px; font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 14px; }

      .cta-row {
        display: flex;
        gap: 14px;
        margin-top: 28px;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
      }
      .cta {
        display: inline-block;
        padding: 14px 22px;
        border-radius: 6px;
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 14px;
        font-weight: 500;
        border-bottom: none;
      }
      .cta.primary { background: var(--accent); color: #0a0e1a; }
      .cta.primary:hover { background: #7ab1f5; border-bottom: none; }
      .cta.secondary {
        background: transparent;
        color: var(--accent);
        border: 1px solid var(--accent);
      }
      .cta.secondary:hover {
        background: var(--accent-soft);
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--accent);
      }

      footer {
        padding: 48px 0;
        border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
        text-align: center;
        color: var(--text-dim);
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 12px;
      }

      @media (max-width: 600px) {
        body { font-size: 16px; }
        section.hero { padding: 64px 0 40px; }
        ul.feature-list li { flex-direction: column; gap: 4px; }
        ul.feature-list .key { min-width: 0; }
        table.compare, table.pricing { font-size: 13px; }
        table.compare th, table.compare td,
        table.pricing th, table.pricing td { padding: 10px 8px; }
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <header class="site-header">
      <div class="container row">
        <span class="brand">skydock</span>
        <nav class="nav">
          <a href="#problem">Problem</a>
          <a href="#product">Product</a>
          <a href="#how">How it works</a>
          <a href="#pricing">Subscription tiers</a>
          <a href="#faq">FAQ</a>
          <a href="#pilot">Closed-loop pilot</a>
        </nav>
      </div>
    </header>

    <main>
      <section class="hero">
        <div class="container">
          <h1>Close your safety case faster.</h1>
          <p class="tagline">{tagline}</p>
          <p class="subline">{subline}</p>
          <div class="hero-meta">
            <span><span class="label">product</span>Library subscription</span>
            <span><span class="label">format</span>OpenSCENARIO 2.0 + OpenLABEL</span>
            <span><span class="label">pilot</span>Free 30-day closed-loop eval</span>
            <span><span class="label">conversion</span>Pre-agreed success criteria</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="problem">
        <div class="container">
          <h2>The problem</h2>
          <h3>The safety case has a ground-truth problem that synthetic data can't fix.</h3>
          <p>
            Every AV company shipping in 2026 has the same gate to clear:
            a closed-loop collision-rate evaluation against a library of
            high-criticality scenarios, segmented by criticality bin, that
            regulators and internal safety leadership both sign off on.
          </p>
          <p>
            Three structural problems are stuck in that gate:
          </p>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li>
              <span class="key">circular ground truth</span>
              <span class="val">Synthetic scenario libraries (world models, generative sims, replay rigs trained on your own captures) inherit the assumptions of the system being validated. They cannot serve as <em>independent</em> evidence in a safety case, by construction. NHTSA AV STEP, EU AI Act, and UK CCAV all increasingly require independent validation data.</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="key">coverage gaps you can't see</span>
              <span class="val">Your library has gaps where your fleet doesn't drive, doesn't drive at the right times, or where your ego perception can't see the interaction at all (occluded by your own vehicle, lower vantage point, narrow FOV). The gaps shape your collision-rate eval result without showing up in your coverage report.</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="key">long-tail scenarios are filtered, not mined</span>
              <span class="val">Customers need <em>real</em>, high-criticality scenarios with rarity signals their QA team can filter on. Raw drone clips are commodity; a criticality-scored, epistemic-uncertainty-tagged, corpus-frequency-ranked library is the artifact safety teams actually use. We sell the filtered library, not the bucket of clips.</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="product">
        <div class="container">
          <h2>The product</h2>
          <h3>An always-on aerial BEV scenario library, criticality-scored, filterable by your OpenODD axes.</h3>
          <p>
            Skydock operates a growing network of fixed-point aerial capture
            installations at high-incident US intersections. Every captured
            scenario runs through a 5-signal curation pipeline. The filtered,
            scored, taxonomy-tagged library is exposed to subscribers via API
            and via partner integrations (Foretellix, Applied Intuition
            Validation Toolset, CARLA).
          </p>
          <p>
            You don't buy a fixed set of clips. You subscribe to the library
            and query it for the scenarios that match your evolving safety
            case &mdash; criticality bin, scene class, agent count, geography,
            time-of-day, weather, OpenODD-axis match.
          </p>
          <div class="deliverable-card">
            <span class="tree-line">scenario_skydock-cap-00042/</span><br>
            <span class="tree-line">├─</span> <span class="file">metadata.json</span>           <span class="desc">site ID · capture geometry · scene class · OpenLABEL tags · 5-signal curation scores · OpenODD axis match</span><br>
            <span class="tree-line">├─</span> <span class="file">agent_tracks.json</span>       <span class="desc">per-frame ENU positions of every visible vehicle / pedestrian / cyclist at 30 fps, with heading and speed</span><br>
            <span class="tree-line">├─</span> <span class="file">scenario.xosc</span>           <span class="desc">OpenSCENARIO 2.0 export — road network reference, scenario entities, storyboard skeleton</span><br>
            <span class="tree-line">└─</span> <span class="file">raw_video.mp4</span>           <span class="desc">optional 4K H.265 source video — toggleable in subscription tier</span>
          </div>
          <p class="dim">
            The library grows continuously: ~1,000 newly-delivered scenarios
            per site per month after the curation filter. At 5 active sites
            (Year 1 target) that's ~60,000 net-new scored scenarios per year
            added to the corpus all subscribers can query.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="evidence">
        <div class="container">
          <h2>The evidence</h2>
          <h3>Why aerial BEV is the validation data type that survives the world-model era.</h3>
          <p>
            Two distinct claims worth separating: <strong>aerial drone data
            improves AV models in the lab</strong> (published research),
            and <strong>aerial drone data is the validation data type with
            durable willingness-to-pay</strong> (the V2 thesis). Both matter,
            but the second is what we sell.
          </p>
          <p class="dim" style="margin-top: 6px; margin-bottom: 18px;">
            <strong>What the research says about aerial BEV in training and
            validation:</strong> highD trajectories drove published RMSE
            reductions of 64% on EPN and 18-72% on Velocity Vector Field
            architectures. Curated long-tail training reduced collision
            rate in simulation from 16.0% to 5.5% (Mining the Long Tail,
            arXiv 2508.18397). Aerial pedestrian detection reaches 99.7%
            accuracy versus 30-50% under ego-perspective occlusion. These
            results come from the open published datasets we model our
            curation pipeline after.
          </p>
          <p class="dim">
            <strong>What we tell customers honestly:</strong> the
            customer-specific magnitude of any model-performance gain
            comes from <em>your</em> closed-loop pilot on <em>your</em>
            safety case. The structural argument for why aerial BEV
            should help is not in question. What's worth measuring
            against your own held-out collision-rate eval is the magnitude.
            That's what the free pilot is for.
          </p>
          <p>
            The durable layer of the pitch is the second claim. Three
            independent reasons aerial BEV is the validation data class
            with growing &mdash; not shrinking &mdash; willingness-to-pay:
          </p>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li>
              <span class="key">regulation requires it</span>
              <span class="val">NHTSA AV STEP (Dec 2024 NPRM, finalized 2025), EU AI Act high-risk system requirements, UK CCAV safety-case process &mdash; each is moving in the same direction: independent validation evidence is mandatory for production AV deployment. Synthetic data fails the "independent" requirement by construction.</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="key">world models can't substitute</span>
              <span class="val">Wayve GAIA-3, NVIDIA Cosmos, and synthetic generators are manufacturing infinite training data &mdash; eroding training-data willingness-to-pay every generation. But closed-loop validation requires <em>real, independent ground truth</em> the model has not seen. Synthetic libraries fail the circularity test.</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="key">tied to revenue, not R&amp;D</span>
              <span class="val">Faster safety-case closure equals faster commercial deployment equals direct revenue impact for your AV deployment. Validation data is not a research line-item; it's on the critical path to launch.</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="why">
        <div class="container">
          <h2>Why this is hard to solve internally</h2>
          <h3>The existing alternatives, and why they don't fill the safety-case gap.</h3>
