            <li>
              <div class="faq-q">What's actually different about a "validation-grade" library vs raw drone clips?</div>
              <div class="faq-a">Three things. (1) 5-signal curation: every scenario is scored on criticality, epistemic uncertainty, corpus frequency, multi-agent interaction density, and scene-class taxonomy match. (2) OpenLABEL + OpenSCENARIO 2.0 native format that drops into your closed-loop sim without conversion. (3) OpenODD axis tagging so you can query the library against your coverage model. Raw clips are commodity; the scored, tagged, queryable library is the artifact safety teams actually use.</div>
            </li>
            <li>
              <div class="faq-q">How does the closed-loop pilot work in practice?</div>
              <div class="faq-a">100 free criticality-scored scenarios from a Bay Area intersection you specify, delivered in OpenSCENARIO 2.0. You measure your AV's collision rate on your existing held-out eval before and after adding the scenarios. Success criteria are jointly authored before the pilot starts &mdash; typically a ≥10% collision-rate reduction in at least one criticality bin, or coverage-gap closure on ≥3 OpenODD axes. Conversion to subscription happens if the agreed criteria are met.</div>
            </li>
            <li>
              <div class="faq-q">What if your sites don't cover the intersections we care about?</div>
              <div class="faq-a">Custom site deployment: you specify a high-criticality intersection in your operating area; we deploy a Model A/B/C site at $50K-$150K setup. Capture for 6-12 months, then folds into your library subscription. Site selection is one of our highest-leverage decisions, so customer demand signal weights heavily on what we build next.</div>
            </li>
            <li>
              <div class="faq-q">How does Skydock data interact with my synthetic pipeline?</div>
              <div class="faq-a">We deliver native OpenSCENARIO 2.0 + OpenLABEL &mdash; drops into Foretellix, Applied Intuition, CARLA, Cognata, or your internal validation pipeline without schema rewrite. Real aerial captures can also seed synthetic generators (Parallel Domain, Mira) as input for hyper-realistic digital twins. The synthetic pipeline complements our real captures; it doesn't replace them in the safety case.</div>
            </li>
            <li>
              <div class="faq-q">Can my library access be exclusive &mdash; not licensed to competitors?</div>
              <div class="faq-a">Default library subscription is multi-tenant (which is what keeps prices low). Time-bounded exclusivity on specific captures or specific sites available at 2-5× premium for safety-case-sensitive deployments. Enterprise tier includes exclusivity windows by default.</div>
            </li>
            <li>
              <div class="faq-q">How do you handle pedestrian privacy and license plates?</div>
              <div class="faq-a">Default delivery is anonymized agent tracks (position + class + heading + speed) &mdash; no biometric or PII data. Optional raw 4K video has face and license-plate blurring applied before delivery, compliant with California Civil Code §1708.8, CCPA, and AB 856. Custom privacy handling negotiable for enterprise customers with specific compliance requirements.</div>
            </li>
            <li>
              <div class="faq-q">What's your regulatory posture, especially on Part 107 and Remote ID?</div>
              <div class="faq-a">Skydock holds the FAA Part 107 commercial certificate; per-site operators hold individual remote pilot certificates. Model A (rooftop) and Model B (tethered drone) operate within standard Part 107 envelope; tethered drones have simplified registration and Remote ID exemption. Model C (drone-in-a-box) requires BVLOS waiver &mdash; filed M1 of operations and tracked as a milestone in our execution plan. We do not rely on sub-250g Remote ID exemption for commercial ops; that exemption is for recreational flight, not commercial Part 107.</div>
            </li>
            <li>
              <div class="faq-q">What happens to the library if a site goes offline?</div>
              <div class="faq-a">Per-site uptime targets ≥95% of operational-envelope hours captured. Outages past 72 hours trigger pro-rated subscription credit. Library subscribers retain access to all already-captured scenarios from a site even if the site is paused or decommissioned.</div>
            </li>
            <li>
              <div class="faq-q">Do you carry insurance for the drone operations?</div>
              <div class="faq-a">Yes. Commercial drone liability insurance per FAA Part 107 &mdash; $1M standard coverage. Production and Enterprise subscribers can request higher coverage limits in the master service agreement. We carry the regulatory and accident liability so you don't have to take it onto your books.</div>
            </li>
            <li>
              <div class="faq-q">How does pricing scale with corpus growth?</div>
              <div class="faq-a">Subscription pricing locks for the 12-month term at signing. Renewal pricing reflects net-new corpus value (more sites, more scenarios, more curation depth) but expansion to next tier is at your option. You're not penalized for the library getting bigger; you choose whether to subscribe to more of it.</div>
            </li>
            <li>
              <div class="faq-q">What's the difference between Skydock and levelXdata?</div>
              <div class="faq-a">Three things. (1) US geographic coverage (vs Germany-only). (2) Continuous library growth (vs one-time research collections). (3) 5-signal curation scoring + OpenODD axis tagging (vs raw trajectory dumps). levelXdata is the validated commercial precedent that proves the category works at unit-economic scale; we're the US-coverage, validation-grade, continuously-growing extension of that model.</div>
            </li>
          </ul>
